
Overview of adj convulsive

The adj convulsive has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) convulsive, spasmodic, spastic -- (affected by involuntary jerky muscular contractions; resembling a spasm; "convulsive motions"; "his body made a spasmodic jerk"; "spastic movements")
2. (1) convulsive -- (resembling a convulsion in being sudden and violent; "a convulsive rage"; "convulsive laughter")
